<DATE_TIME> 2000-06-07 00:10 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Rapper Charged After Michigan Fight  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   DETROIT (AP) -- Rapper Eminem was charged Tuesday with two felony
weapons counts stemming from a weekend fight which prosecutors say
started after the Grammy winner saw another man kissing his wife.
</P>
<P>
   Eminem is charged with one count of carrying a concealed weapon
and one count of assault with a deadly weapon, said Macomb County
Prosecutor Carl Marlinga.
</P>
<P>
   The 27-year-old performer, whose real name is Marshall Bruce
Mathers III, is expected to be arraigned Wednesday in Warren
District Court.
</P>
<P>
   The fight happened about 2:20 a.m. Sunday in the parking lot of
a bar in Warren, the rapper's hometown.
</P>
<P>
   Marlinga said Eminem hit John Guerra over the head with a 9mm
Smith &AMP; Wesson gun after he saw Guerra kissing his wife, Kimberly
Mathers, 27. The gun was not loaded, he said.
</P>
<P>
   Kimberly Mathers told the Detroit Free Press her husband
''overreacted'' to a friendly kiss between friends.
</P>
<P>
   Eminem's lawyer, Howard Hertz, said his client planned to let
the judge enter an innocent plea for him in court Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
   In February, Eminem won a Grammy for best rap album for his
debut release, ''The Slim Shady LP,'' and another Grammy for best
rap solo performance for the hit single ''My Name Is.''
</P>
<P>
   Eminem has the No. 1 album in the country, ''The Marshall
Mathers LP.''
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
