<HEADLINE> Wall St. Stocks Up in Early Trading  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEW YORK (AP) -- Stock prices were slightly higher in early
trading.
</P>
<P>
   The Dow Jones Industrial Average was up 16 points in the early
going. Advancing issues on the New York Stock Exchange held a 6-5
lead over decliners.
</P>
<P>
   The Nasdaq Composite Index was ahead 10 points and the Standard
&AMP; Poor's 500 Stock Index was up 5 points.
</P>
<P>
   Stocks are showing no real sign of breaking out of the quiet
trading that has marked the past two sessions.
</P>
<P>
   Analysts say there's been a need for the market to catch its
breath after last week's furious advance.
</P>
<P>
   And the lack of any market-moving news has helped them in that
regard.
</P>
<P>
   At this point, some investors may be content to wait until
Friday's release of the May producer price index before taking on
any new significant positions.
</P>
<P>
   One sector that could see some activity today is the airlines,
on reports of possible further consolidation in the industry.
</P>
