<DOCTYPE> NEWS STORY </DOCTYPE>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-06-07 12:35 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Celebrity Spotlight &AMP; Birthdays  </HEADLINE>
By The Associated Press	   
<TEXT>
<P>
   In the birthday spotlight:
</P>
<P>
   For someone who says he isn't worried about building a career,
Joshua Jackson is well on his way. Jackson, who was born on June
11, 1978, is familiar to TV audiences as Pacey on the WB network's
''Dawson's Creek.'' He had two new films this spring: ''The
Skulls'' and ''Gossip.'' ''I have high expectations of myself as a
person, but my ambition is more to succeed as a human being than a
business entity,'' Jackson says.
</P>
<P>
   Ally Sheedy is back in business after more than a decade of
living with irrelevance. ''There was a whole period of time when I
just could not get seen for a job,'' says Sheedy, who was born on
June 13, 1962. Now a slew of edgy, indie roles has brought renewed
attention to the star of the 1985 film ''The Breakfast Club.'' She
won the National Society of Film Critics' best actress award for
her role in the 1998 film ''High Art.'' She played the part of a
lesbian drug addict. ''As far as my career is concerned, as far as
my work is concerned, 'High Art' is the best thing that ever
happened to me,'' she says.
</P>
<P>
   Celebrity birthdays June 11-17:
</P>
<P>
   June 11: Actor Gene Wilder is 65. Actor Chad Everett is 64.
Musician Frank Beard of ZZ Top is 51. Musician Dan Lavery of Tonic
is 31. Actor Joshua Jackson is 22.
</P>
<P>
   June 12: Singer Vic Damone is 72. Actor-singer Jim Nabors is 70.
Musician Bun E. Carlos of Cheap Trick is 49. Actor Timothy Busfield
is 43. Musician John Linnell of They Might Be Giants is 41. Rapper
Grandmaster Dee of Whodini is 38.
</P>
<P>
   June 13: Actor Malcolm McDowell is 57. Singer Dennis Locorriere
of Dr. Hook is 51. Actor Richard Thomas is 49. Comedian Tim Allen
is 47. Actress Ally Sheedy is 38. Actresses Ashley and Mary Kate
