<HEADLINE> Stone's Ex-Maid Jailed for Theft  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   LOS ANGELES (AP) -- Sharon Stone's former housekeeper was
sentenced to 16 months in prison after pleading no contest to
taking pricey handbags, shoes, jewelry and other goods from the
actress.
</P>
<P>
   Judge Victoria Chavez also ordered Socorro ''Coco'' Del Carmen
Membrano to pay Stone as much as $50,000 in restitution.
</P>
<P>
   Stone, who wasn't in court Tuesday for the case's disposition,
has said she was hurt by the actions of the woman she had all but
considered a family member.
</P>
<P>
   Membrano, 48, pleaded no contest to a single count of receiving
stolen property. Among the items reported taken were dozens of
evening gowns, including one worth $20,000.
</P>
<P>
   Authorities said Stone noticed things missing over the years and
would occasionally ask Membrano if she knew where they were.
</P>
<P>
   ''The housekeeper would say, 'You gave that to your sister,' or,
'Oh, that's at the cleaners,''' said Deputy District Attorney Wendy
E. Segall.
</P>
<P>
   The actress finally learned the truth, authorities said, after
other staffers saw the items stuffed into eight garbage bags at
Membrano's home.
</P>
</TEXT>
