<DATE_TIME> 2000-06-07 13:39 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Adoption Hurdles Highlighted  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   WASHINGTON (AP) -- A bipartisan group of lawmakers is hoping to
draw attention to the bureaucratic maze that surrounds the adoption
process and spur Congress to action.
</P>
<P>
   Wednesday's events to raise awareness featured an appeal by
Wendy's founder Dave Thomas and an exhibit in a House office
building with pictures detailing the struggles facing foster
children and families attempting to adopt. Thomas was adopted as a
child and has founded the Dave Thomas Foundation for Adoption.
</P>
<P>
   ''We're hoping to demonstrate the difficulty children have
finding their way to a permanent family,'' said Sen. Mary Landrieu,
D-La. ''We have made it much more difficult than it should be.''
</P>
<P>
   Said Thomas, ''Every day a child waits in the foster care system
is one day too long. They're losing their childhood.''
</P>
<P>
   According to the National Adoption Information Clearinghouse, 72
percent of children awaiting adoption have been stuck in the foster
care system for two years or longer. Approximately 117,000 children
are waiting for adoption.
</P>
<P>
   Landrieu and Republican Sens. Chuck Grassley of Iowa and Mike
DeWine of Ohio are introducing adoption legislation that includes a
bonus to states for placing children in an adoptive home within
three years.
------
</P>
<P>
   On the Net: http://www.adopt.org
</P>
</TEXT>
