<HEADLINE> Police say teen charged in baby's death couldn't find sitter  </HEADLINE>
AP Photo
<TEXT>
<P>
   PATERSON, N.J. (AP) - Police found the body of a 16-month-old
boy in the Passaic River on Wednesday, 2 1/2 miles from the spot
authorities say his mother threw him in the water when she couldn't
find a babysitter.
</P>
<P>
   Police found the body at 12:05 p.m. about two miles downstream
from the Great Falls, said Boris Moczula, Passaic County's first
assistant prosecutor.
</P>
<P>
   The baby was wearing a red and blue sweat suit and a diaper,
Moczula said. An autopsy was planned to determine cause of death.
</P>
