she is a juvenile, was arraigned Tuesday on charges of juvenile
delinquency stemming from the alleged murder.
</P>
<P>
   Officers began searching for the body Monday morning after
detectives notified them that the girl had hurled her child off a
footbridge when she failed to find a baby sitter, authorities said.
</P>
<P>
   Authorities said after throwing the baby into the water, the
teen-age mother went to visit her boyfriend for several hours
before returning home. It is unclear whether she told anyone what
she had done with the child, including the father.
</P>
<P>
   Authorities said the baby's father is no longer dating the
mother, but was still involved in his son's life and cared for the
child several times a week while the baby's mother went to night
school.
</P>
<P>
   The young mother drove to St. Joseph's Hospital and Medical
Center late Sunday night to seek treatment for problems ''of a
psychiatric nature'' and while there revealed what had happened to
her child, Purdy said.
</P>
<P>
   Moczula said authorities have not decided whether to charge the
girl as an adult.
</P>
<P>
   The girl's attorney, Anthony Fusco, said there is no case
against her.
</P>
<P>
   ''All they have is a statement that probably isn't admissible,
and I'm not so sure that she gave a statement that's even true,''
Fusco said.
