<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Practice Bomb Lands Near SC Factory  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   SUMTER, S.C. (AP) -- An F-16 fighter jet released a practice bomb
off target, dropping it just outside a battery factory Wednesday, a
spokesman for the McEntire Air National Guard Base in Eastover
said.
</P>
<P>
   No one was injured when the practice bomb slammed into the
ground in an open field near the Yuasa Corp. plant south of Sumter.
The bomb carried the explosive charge of a shotgun shell and smoked
to indicate where it landed.
</P>
<P>
   The F-16 was supposed to drop it during a training run near the
Manchester State Forest about 10 miles away, said Maj. Les Carroll.
</P>
<P>
   ''It was just what we call an inadvertent release,'' he said.
</P>
<P>
   Carroll said military officials had ruled out pilot error, but
were still trying to figure out why the practice bomb fell off
target.
</P>
</TEXT>
