<DATE_TIME> 2000-06-07 21:32 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Blue Jays' Greene Hurt After Stint  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   ATLANTA (AP) -- Toronto's Todd Greene filled in at his old
position and wound up on the disabled list Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
   Greene, who has been playing outfield for the Blue Jays, was
forced into duty at catcher Tuesday night when Alberto Castillo was
ejected for arguing a called third strike in the fifth inning. The
Blue Jays' other catcher, Darrin Fletcher, is plagued by a sore
shoulder.
</P>
<P>
   Greene, while making a throw to second, caught his right spikes
in the dirt and strained a knee ligament in the seventh inning.
Fletcher was forced to work the final two innings behind the plate
despite his injury.
</P>
<P>
   Greene was placed on the 15-day DL, his spot on the roster taken
by catcher Josh Phelps, who was called up from Double-A Knoxville.
</P>
<P>
   Once considered Anaheim's catcher of the future, Greene battled
shoulder problems and was released in spring training by the
Angels. He was no longer able to catch regularly after hitting .243
with 14 homers and 42 RBIs last season.
</P>
<P>
   Greene signed with the Blue Jays and was assigned to Triple-A
Syracuse, where he hit .297 with seven home runs and 14 RBIs before
being called up May 19. Greene is hitting .273 with one homer and
one RBI in five games for Toronto.
</P>
<P>
   Fletcher, who hurt his shoulder while making a throw to second
last weekend, hopes to be able to catch regularly by Friday's game
against Montreal.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
