<HEADLINE> Mariners Option Hodges to Tacoma  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   SEATTLE (AP) -- Right-hander Kevin Hodges will be optioned from
Seattle to Triple-A Tacoma, and the Mariners will recall
infielder-outfielder Charles Gipson.
</P>
<P>
   The moves, expected to be announced Thursday, leave the Mariners
with 11 pitchers.
</P>
<P>
   In six games this season, Hodges is 0-0 with a 3.52 ERA in 7 2-3
innings.
</P>
<P>
   Gipson ''gives us some speed off the bench and that extra
infielder we haven't had,'' Mariners manager Lou Piniella said.
</P>
</TEXT>
