<DATE_TIME> 2000-06-07 21:35 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Baseball All-Star Staffs Chosen  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEW YORK (AP) -- Managers Lou Piniella of the Seattle Mariners
and Larry Rothschild of the Tampa Bay Devil Rays were picked
Wednesday as coaches for the American League All-Star team, which
will be managed by Joe Torre of the New York Yankees.
</P>
<P>
   Torre also invited seven members of his Yankees staff -- Mike
Borzello, Chris Chambliss, Tony Cloninger, Lee Mazzilli, Willie
Randolph, Mel Stottlemyre and Don Zimmer -- to handle batting
practice and other field duties.
</P>
<P>
   The AL trainers will be Jamie Reed of Tampa Bay and Mark
Anderson of the Chicago White Sox.
</P>
<P>
   National League manager Bobby Cox of the Atlanta Braves selected
Houston Astros manager Larry Dierker and Arizona Diamondbacks
manager Buck Showalter as coaches.
</P>
<P>
   Cox also asked his coaching staff -- Pat Corrales, Bobby Dews,
Glenn Hubbard, Leo Mazzone, Merv Rettenmund and Ned Yost -- to join
him at this year's All-Star game.
</P>
<P>
   Dave Pursley of the Braves and Brad Henderson of the St. Louis
Cardinals will be the NL trainers.
</P>
<P>
   The game will be played July 11 at Turner Field in Atlanta.
</P>
</TEXT>
