<DATE_TIME> 2000-06-07 21:39 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Rangers Send Johnson to Minors  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   ARLINGTON, Texas (AP) -- Reliever Jonathan Johnson was optioned
to Triple-A Oklahoma on Wednesday by the Texas Rangers after he
pitched three innings in an 11-6 loss to Los Angeles.
</P>
<P>
   Johnson's spot on the Texas roster will likely be filled by
outfielder Gabe Kapler, who was scheduled to finished a three-game
rehabilitation stint with Double-A Tulsa on Wednesday night.
</P>
<P>
   Kapler has been on the disabled list since May 4 with a tear in
his upper right quadriceps. He is expected to rejoin the Rangers on
Friday, when they begin a nine-game trip with three games at
Colorado.
</P>
<P>
   Johnson was called up Tuesday to replace Ryan Glynn, who made a
spot start for the Rangers on Monday night and then was sent back
to Oklahoma. Glynn pitched eight shutout innings and allowed just
two hits as Texas beat Los Angeles 2-0 for its only win in the
three-game series.
</P>
<P>
   In his only appearance with the Rangers, Johnson allowed two
unearned runs and three hits.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
