<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Abdullah Fastest in Rowing Trials  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   CAMDEN, N.J. (AP) -- Top-seeded Aquil Abdullah, a silver medalist
in the Pan Am Games, posted the fastest time in men's singles
sculls Wednesday as the U.S. Rowing Olympic Team Trials got under
way.
</P>
<P>
   Thirty-three men competed on the Cooper River with 16 advancing
to Thursday's second round of heats.
</P>
<P>
   Abdullah completed the 2,000-meter course in 6 minutes, 47.6
seconds.
</P>
<P>
   Steve Gillespie, the No. 3 seed, finished second in the time
trial in 6:50.7, edging No. 2 seed Don Smith, 6:51.5. Erik Miller
(6:52.5) finished fourth and Jim Neil (6:53.2) was fifth.
</P>
<P>
   Gerard Sweeney became the 16th and final sculler to qualify for
Thursday's heats, doing so by .01 seconds.
</P>
<P>
   Nine events will be contested at the six-day trials, including
the men's and women's single sculls, men's and women's double
sculls, men's and women's lightweight double sculls, men's and
women's pair, and the men's quadruple sculls.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
