<HEADLINE> Yankees 7, Expos 2  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   MONTREAL (AP) -- Orlando Hernandez allowed four hits in eight
innings and the New York Yankees stole a season-high five bases
Wednesday night in a 7-2 win over the Montreal Expos.
</P>
<P>
   Hernandez (6-4), who pitched his first career complete game at
Montreal on June 9, 1998 in his only previous start against the
Expos, allowed one hit in the first five innings -- Vladimir
Guerrero's 18th homer, a two-run drive the first.
</P>
<P>
