   Tari Phillips added 20 points and 10 rebounds for New York
(2-3), which dealt the Shock (1-2) their second straight loss.
</P>
<P>
   Dominique Canty led Detroit with a career-best 22 points,
including 14 as the Shock took a 37-34 halftime lead.
</P>
<P>
   Phillips and Johnson combined for 26 points in the first half
for New York, and the rest of the team managed only eight.
</P>
<P>
   Phillips cut Detroit's lead to one with the opening basket of
the second half, but New York wasn't able to go ahead until Tamika
Whitmore's three-point play made it 56-55 with 9:48 left.
</P>
