<HEADLINE> Federal agents seize documents from rail contractor  </HEADLINE>
prtv
<TEXT>
<P>
   OLD SAYBROOK, Conn. (AP) - Federal agents on Wednesday raided
the joint offices of two contractors responsible for electrifying
the high-speed Amtrak rail line between New York and Boston,
seizing cartons of documents and computers.
</P>
<P>
   The Balfour Beatty Construction Inc. and Massachusetts Electric
Construction Co. have been criticized for cost overruns on the
project. The price tag has ballooned from $321 million to over $600
million.
</P>
<P>
   The Office of Inspector General, the agency in charge of
investigating Amtrak, would not comment on the investigation.
Balfour Beatty officials also refused to talk about the raid.
</P>
</TEXT>
